    "en": {
      "title": "A revelation from Welgama about an invisible force",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Kumara Welgama, Kalutara District Member of the Samagi Jana Balavega, said in the Parliament that an invisible force is pulling the President's leg.",
        "Mr. Welgama said that it is not the Members of Parliament who are dragging their feet like that and the Members like the President.",
        "Mr. Kumara Welgama said that if the President's proposals are implemented, the invisible force will be displeased and if there are corrupt people, he will tell the President not to give them positions.",
        "\"Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe's budget is really good. It is a budget suitable for today's times. I don't know if this can be implemented? I don't know if it is possible. The budget gap is 100 percent. We have to borrow for it.",
        "The only thing that happened in the last budget was hitting the table. They say that it will not happen this time. I think Mr. Ranil Wickramasinghe will do the job as a generous politician,\" said Mr. Welgama.",
        "The MP said that he is not going to join the government and that he has not been a minister for seven years and now he has no need to be a minister, but to build the country, we should get rid of the differences and come together.",
        "Countries like China and America are helping with great hopes, but India has currently given 4 billion dollars in aid and we should bow our hands to \"our big brother\" and it seems that \"big brother and younger brothers\" are taking good care of them, joining the budget debate in the Parliament. Mr. Kumara Welgama mentioned."
      ],
